1
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,240
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,440
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,400
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
[Episode 16]

23
00:01:34,760 --> 00:01:36,130
I know what you're about to say.

24
00:01:40,760 --> 00:01:41,660
Just head back.

25
00:01:42,790 --> 00:01:43,460
I want

26
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,570
to be alone for a bit.

27
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:49,980
Alright.

28
00:01:52,590 --> 00:01:53,690
I'll get going then.

29
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:32,940
After my mentor passed,

30
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:34,660
I couldn't shake the feeling

31
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:37,500
that I'd let him down.

32
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:41,130
So I didn't dare slow down,

33
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:42,570
didn't dare stop.

34
00:02:44,030 --> 00:02:45,890
Like if I just held on a little longer,

35
00:02:47,590 --> 00:02:49,410
maybe the guilt would ease up.

36
00:02:52,870 --> 00:02:54,130
Mr. Chen.

37
00:02:55,310 --> 00:02:55,820
Yeah?

38
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,130
It's our day off.

39
00:02:57,150 --> 00:02:58,130
And you dragged us

40
00:02:58,150 --> 00:02:59,380
out here this early?

41
00:02:59,590 --> 00:03:01,730
You're young. Why sleep so much?

42
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,220
We're picking up trash.

43
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:04,850
The fish out there need it.

44
00:03:04,910 --> 00:03:06,850
It might look like
we're just cleaning up garbage,

45
00:03:07,590 --> 00:03:09,220
but in a way,

46
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:12,850
we're saving a life in the ocean.

47
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,660
Same as the work we do

48
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,060
in Passenger Inspection.

49
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:19,610
Look.

50
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,170
Up ahead.

51
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:24,130
See that? We're not doing this alone.

52
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,780
Plenty of people will join us.

53
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:28,340
So I believe

54
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:30,660
as long as we keep going,

55
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,540
one day,

56
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:34,850
this whole beach will be clean.

57
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,260
And

58
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:38,340
if I can't come out here much later on,

59
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:39,850
you all need

60
00:03:39,870 --> 00:03:41,220
to hold your post.

61
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:44,500
Come back often
and pick up what you can.

62
00:03:44,590 --> 00:03:46,610
Looking out at this endless ocean,

63
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:49,060
I finally understand

64
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:52,130
why my mentor brought us here
to clean the beach.

65
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,540
There's only ever been

66
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:58,260
one thing we're meant to do.

67
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,660
To guard the country's gate.

68
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:03,570
It takes a whole team
to keep it going.

69
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,940
Even if there are regrets along the way,

70
00:04:07,710 --> 00:04:09,940
we still shouldn't rush it.

71
00:04:10,310 --> 00:04:11,500
Just keep going.

72
00:04:28,630 --> 00:04:30,140
♪Turn around and look♪

73
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:34,700
♪That door's still open♪

74
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:37,810
♪Waiting there for you♪

75
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:44,480
You're back, son.

76
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:45,320
Cong.

77
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:46,000
You're back.

78
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:47,920
Where have you been?

79
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,960
Look at you.

80
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,120
Go change your clothes.

81
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:51,020
Leave your shoes outside.

82
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:56,600
Mom,

83
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:58,200
can I get a glass of water?

84
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:58,880
I'm parched.

85
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:00,280
Look at him.

86
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:01,640
Still like a kid.

87
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:04,080
Don't you think
he's in a much better mood?

88
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:05,760
Oh, right.

89
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:08,600
That singing in the hallway,
was that him?

90
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:09,440
Sounded like him.

91
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:12,440
If that's the case,

92
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:13,720
I can

93
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:15,080
finally relax.

94
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:21,800
Here.

95
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:23,320
Thanks, Mom.

96
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:24,600
Cong,

97
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,840
did you just get back from Fei's place?

98
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:29,680
I cleaned up trash on the beach.

99
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:30,440
Clean the beach?

100
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:31,400
Why?

101
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,200
To protect the ocean.

102
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,240
My mentor's last wish.

103
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:36,880
Right.

104
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,920
Passport, visa, all sorted.

105
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:40,520
Here.

106
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:49,160
I can't go.

107
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:52,800
What?

108
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:54,320
Customs didn't approve it?

109
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,320
It's not like that.

110
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:58,400
The trip was never really my idea.

111
00:05:58,640 --> 00:06:00,680
Sometimes you just want some quiet.

112
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:01,680
To be on your own.

113
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:03,960
You suggested Australia,

114
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:05,720
saying it's far

115
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:07,640
and good for me to make a fresh start.

116
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:08,400
I thought

117
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:08,920
it made sense,

118
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:10,320
so I said yes.

119
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:11,960
But now, I've thought it through.

120
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:13,040
I don't want to go anymore.

121
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:14,960
I'll go talk

122
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:17,080
to Customs

123
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:18,520
and withdraw the application.

124
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:21,000
You're not going abroad?

125
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:23,760
I need to get back to work.

126
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:25,000
Cong,

127
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:28,600
did you forget your mentor's last wish?

128
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:29,880
He told you to leave.

129
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:33,680
Good thing I didn't hear that
from him myself.

130
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:35,920
I've thought about a lot.

131
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,800
I recalled many things from before.

132
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:40,040
Recalled how he pushed me
and had my back.

133
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,280
He used to tell me all the time

134
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:44,080
I had to guard
this country's gate for him,

135
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,200
stand every post in his place,

136
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:48,960
and never disgrace this uniform.

137
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:51,560
And the thing is,

138
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,360
when I was quitting,

139
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,720
he didn't give up on me.

140
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,240
When he told me to quit,

141
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:00,840
I don't think
that's what he really meant.

142
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:01,800
You know how he was.

143
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,320
He must be confused again.

144
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,320
Clear one minute, confused the next.

145
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:06,400
We couldn't always tell.

146
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:07,800
That makes sense.

147
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,080
Also,

148
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:12,120
even if the illness wore him down,

149
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:13,320
made him lose hope,

150
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,280
and he did want me to quit,

151
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:16,040
I still wouldn't

152
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:17,600
because I truly

153
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:19,520
love this job

154
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:20,880
in Passenger Inspection.

155
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:24,080
Not just for you

156
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:25,680
or my mom,

157
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,840
but for all those families out there.

158
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,520
I must hold this line.

159
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:29,920
Right?

160
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:31,000
I'm gonna take a shower.

161
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:32,880
Son,

162
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,440
well said.

163
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:35,920
I almost want to clap for you.

164
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:37,880
Cong,

165
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:40,960
if you've really made up your mind,
then go do it.

166
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:42,400
Alright.

167
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,080
Hey.

168
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,880
Have Cong put his passport
and visa away.

169
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,320
I've been tied up with his stuff.

170
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:51,640
Look at the good weather.

171
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,240
I haven't been fishing these days.

172
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,160
That's a real loss.

173
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:55,800
I'm gonna go wet a line.

174
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:56,900
- Alright, take care. - Yeah.

175
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:16,720
Yu,

176
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:19,240
it's been days.

177
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:20,720
Mr. Guo still hasn't come back.

178
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:21,960
Does he really…

179
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:22,440
No.

180
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:24,920
He just needs time.

181
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,560
Then analyze it for me

182
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:29,560
from a psychological angle.

183
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,200
What's going on with him right now?

184
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:35,120
From a psychological angle…

185
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:39,600
He's in that phase

186
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,160
after a belief system collapsed.

187
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:43,840
His sense of identity shakes,

188
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,160
and he is rebuilding it.

189
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:48,520
So going to Fei's place
or leaving the country

190
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,080
is just a kind of withdrawal

191
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:51,600
resulting from his defense mechanisms.

192
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:53,440
But pulling away like that

193
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:55,120
might let him come back stronger.

194
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:57,960
I don't get it.

195
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,400
Stronger or not, it doesn't matter

196
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:00,400
as long as he comes back.

197
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:06,080
Um,

198
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,720
she's not

199
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:09,400
coming over here for us, is she?

200
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:11,760
That doesn't look good.

201
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,960
Tao, where are you flying today?

202
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:20,440
Zhang Yu,

203
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:22,680
are you trying to take Guo Cong from me?

204
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:28,240
I know you like him.

205
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:30,000
You've been sneaking around.

206
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:32,080
I look down on people like that.

207
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:32,920
Hold on, Shen Taotao.

208
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:33,680
Say it straight.

209
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:35,280
What do you mean, sneaking around?

210
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:37,360
He'd already decided to travel,

211
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:39,840
but after you went to see him
at the fish farm,

212
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:42,280
he canceled everything.

213
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,440
Zhang Yu,

214
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:46,400
what did you say to him?

215
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,400
He canceled his trip?

216
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:49,960
Who told you that?

217
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:53,000
Guo Cong.
He told me himself right here.

218
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:54,840
Mr. Guo's at the airport?

219
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:56,160
Sorry.

220
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:56,560
I'll get going.

221
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:59,040
Zhang Yu, I'm not done yet!

222
00:09:59,040 --> 00:09:59,760
Tao,

223
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:00,480
good luck.

224
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,560
If you hadn't come back,

225
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:08,360
Shihuo would be making

226
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:09,960
a whole tribute video for you.

227
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:10,800
That's not true.

228
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:11,720
I trust him.

229
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:13,120
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]
He knows Passenger Inspection

230
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,280
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]
Section I needs him.

231
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,680
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]

232
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:20,920
You're back.

233
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:22,520
Yeah, I'm back.

234
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:24,000
Will you leave again?

235
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:27,760
Not anymore.

236
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,840
Mr. Guo, you're really back.

237
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:35,280
Yu was just telling me earlier

238
00:10:35,640 --> 00:10:38,160
about you pulling away and coming back.

239
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,360
You totally called it.

240
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:40,160
You're amazing!

241
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:42,280
So you really ran off?

242
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:44,000
Now you've come to your senses.

243
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:45,800
That's a good thing.

244
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:46,760
Alright.

245
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:47,920
The briefing's about to start.

246
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:56,600
Hey.

247
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:57,080
What?

248
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,080
Seriously.

249
00:10:58,280 --> 00:10:59,160
Why didn't you tell me

250
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:00,560
Mr. Guo was going back?

251
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:01,800
I just found out, too.

252
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:03,240
I'll let this slide.

253
00:11:03,280 --> 00:11:04,960
Next time, give me a heads-up.

254
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:07,880
Give me that pen.

255
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:15,880
First, I owe everyone an apology.

256
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:17,680
Because of my personal situation,

257
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:19,160
I held up the team's work.

258
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,240
Shihuo said just now

259
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:23,120
that Section I needed me.

260
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:24,840
But honestly,

261
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:27,040
I'm the one who needs Section I.

262
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:29,560
It's been eight years.

263
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:32,360
I went from a clueless rookie

264
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:34,320
to who I am today,

265
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:36,920
someone who's found

266
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:38,160
his place and purpose.

267
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:41,040
That's because of my mentor

268
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:42,240
and

269
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:43,920
all of you.

270
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:45,680
So, thank you.

271
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:48,200
Thank you.

272
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:53,640
We can reuse
that welcome line for Zhang Yu.

273
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:56,480
This time,
let's welcome Guo Cong back home.

274
00:11:56,640 --> 00:11:57,040
Come on.

275
00:11:57,040 --> 00:12:00,440
Welcome back home!

276
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:02,040
Welcome back!

277
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:13,480
Over here.

278
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:15,320
Hello, may I see your passport?

279
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:21,120
Alright, this way, please.

280
00:12:21,560 --> 00:12:22,120
Right this way.

281
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:24,920
No additional duty needed.

282
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:29,200
Cong feels different today.

283
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:30,480
He's smiling so much.

284
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:35,560
Hi, how do I get to the restroom?

285
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:36,280
Over there.

286
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:37,680
Okay. Can we take a photo together?

287
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:39,080
Sorry, no photos allowed here.

288
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:39,880
Thanks. Bye.

289
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:48,880
Mr. Guo seems a little off today.

290
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:54,320
Why is he so happy today?

291
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:54,920
Yeah.

292
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:00,640
Looking sharp, kid.

293
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:02,120
Thanks. Right this way, thank you.

294
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,320
Muyang, come on, let's go.

295
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,280
Hello. I need to inspect your suitcase.

296
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:07,040
Sure.

297
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:08,640
Mom, look.

298
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:09,560
A soldier!

299
00:13:09,640 --> 00:13:11,120
He's a Customs officer.

300
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:13,520
Just like soldiers, he protects us, too.

301
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:15,360
Hi, officer.

302
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:17,720
Hey there. How old are you?

303
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:18,600
Six.

304
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,480
Six already?

305
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:20,560
- You're all grown up. - Mom,

306
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:22,960
when I grow up,
I want to work at Customs, too.

307
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:24,520
Then you'd better study hard

308
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:25,800
so you can get in.

309
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:28,160
When you join us,

310
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:29,920
we'll be guarding the gate together.

311
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:30,680
Okay!

312
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:34,160
Okay.

313
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:35,920
I'll be waiting for you at Customs.

314
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:36,960
Alright, thank you.

315
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:38,000
Bye, officer!

316
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:38,480
Bye.

317
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:51,560
How is it? Everything clear?

318
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:53,000
All clear. Looks good.

319
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:57,800
Mentor,

320
00:13:58,920 --> 00:14:00,520
you've been smiling a lot today.

321
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,640
That's because
I finally feel like I'm needed.

322
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:09,640
Before, all I ever thought about
was catching smugglers.

323
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:13,000
I missed a lot of the simple,
good moments.

324
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:14,120
But today,

325
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:14,880
I saw all of it.

326
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:20,080
Hello.

327
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:23,160
I need to inspect your suitcase.
Thank you.

328
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:26,600
Sorry to keep you waiting.

329
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,600
No worries. Go ahead.

330
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:27,880
Alright.

331
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:40,880
Excuse me,

332
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:42,480
how much salt did you use?

333
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:44,320
Feels like you went all out.

334
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,080
Hey, hey, hey…

335
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,480
It's… it's me, San.

336
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:52,880
Hey,

337
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:54,440
we were in the same detention center.

338
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,000
Hey,

339
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:55,720
it's me.

340
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:56,760
Oh, San.

341
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:00,320
Have a seat.

342
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,320
When'd you get out?

343
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:06,880
A couple of months ago.

344
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:08,800
Thought it was you,

345
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:10,080
so I came over to say hi.

346
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:16,720
How about we grab a bite together?

347
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:18,040
Yeah.

348
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:19,440
Thanks, man.

349
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:21,120
Excuse me,

350
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:23,000
two beers and five kidneys.

351
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:23,760
Got it.

352
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:25,680
Thanks, man.

353
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:28,760
We've been through it together.

354
00:15:32,760 --> 00:15:33,200
San,

355
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:34,520
I've got something to do.

356
00:15:34,880 --> 00:15:35,920
I'll take care of the bill.

357
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:36,880
I'm heading out.

358
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,720
No, no, no.

359
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:40,560
Sit, sit.

360
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:42,400
Please, sit.

361
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:46,240
I

362
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:48,080
came to see you

363
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:49,320
for something serious.

364
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:50,920
You've got business with me?

365
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:54,400
I've got something good.

366
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:55,720
It's fresh.

367
00:15:56,560 --> 00:15:57,640
Need to move it fast.

368
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:02,920
Since when
did you start dealing in that?

369
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:05,120
I just got out.

370
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:06,920
I'm not touching that stuff.

371
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:08,640
Hey,

372
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:10,840
weren't you doing import-export before?

373
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,840
Help me find a buyer overseas.

374
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,600
Ship it out. That's it.

375
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,680
I'll give you 20 percent.

376
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:20,000
Import-export?

377
00:16:21,040 --> 00:16:22,760
You're making me sound legit.

378
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,240
Truth is,

379
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:26,080
I haven't touched

380
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:27,840
that line of work since I got out.

381
00:16:28,560 --> 00:16:29,600
Find someone else.

382
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:31,120
Come on,

383
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:33,360
I don't know anyone like that.

384
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:34,640
How about this?

385
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:36,440
If you really don't want in,

386
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:38,360
just put me in touch with someone solid.

387
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:40,880
I'll give you

388
00:16:41,640 --> 00:16:42,680
ten percent for that.

389
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:56,080
Leave me your number.

390
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,040
If I find someone, I'll let you know.

391
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:00,560
Forget the referral fee.

392
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:03,040
Thanks, man.

393
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:04,320
Let me repeat it again.

394
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:05,920
I'm not getting involved in this.

395
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:07,600
If things blow up,

396
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:09,240
don't drag my name into it.

397
00:17:10,360 --> 00:17:11,560
Don't worry.

398
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:12,960
I know how this works.

399
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:14,960
I'd never set you up.

400
00:17:17,320 --> 00:17:17,680
Alright.

401
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:19,440
Wait for my call.

402
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:21,440
Got it.

403
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:22,440
I'll be waiting for your news.

404
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:12,000
Game over.

405
00:18:16,040 --> 00:18:16,760
Everything sorted?

406
00:18:17,320 --> 00:18:18,160
Yeah, all sorted.

407
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:19,320
Sit, let's talk.

408
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:23,760
It's a Yuan dynasty painting.

409
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:28,360
So what's your next step?

410
00:18:29,560 --> 00:18:31,960
I'll pass the info up the chain

411
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:33,560
and see if they take the job.

412
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:35,320
How are you passing it up?

413
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:36,960
Once you do,

414
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:38,840
how long before you hear back?

415
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:41,280
No clue.

416
00:18:41,640 --> 00:18:43,560
I normally just send it up

417
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:45,160
and wait.

418
00:18:46,320 --> 00:18:47,280
If you pass it up,

419
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:49,760
then it becomes their job.

420
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,680
What do you even get out of that?

421
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:55,920
Come on, I'm just a henchman.

422
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:57,600
Something this big,

423
00:18:57,680 --> 00:18:59,400
it's not my call.

424
00:19:00,520 --> 00:19:01,400
If I were you,

425
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:04,320
I'd take it straight to the top.

426
00:19:05,520 --> 00:19:08,000
Otherwise, you'd stay
at the bottom for life.

427
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:12,080
Alright.

428
00:19:13,240 --> 00:19:14,320
Think it through.

429
00:19:17,560 --> 00:19:18,200
Don't forget

430
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:20,440
to tell me if you hear anything.

431
00:19:20,560 --> 00:19:21,160
Of course.

432
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:22,040
You can count on me.

433
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:22,960
Go.

434
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:25,520
Alright, I'm heading out.

435
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:27,240
See you.

436
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:38,640
Keep playing.

437
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:39,840
Call me if something comes up.

438
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:06,600
Cong.

439
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:07,240
You're back.

440
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:09,400
Where have you been?

441
00:20:09,440 --> 00:20:10,560
Look at you.

442
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:12,480
So when he told me to leave Customs,

443
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:14,760
I don't think
that was what he really meant.

444
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,320
Good thing I didn't hear that
from him myself.

445
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:20,360
Because I truly love this job
in Passenger Inspection.

446
00:20:38,120 --> 00:20:39,360
Not bad, bro.

447
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:40,880
You've already

448
00:20:41,360 --> 00:20:42,840
hooked a few so soon.

449
00:20:44,040 --> 00:20:44,920
Look at me.

450
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:46,200
Nothing.

451
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:49,640
You kept switching spots earlier.

452
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:52,480
It could be the fish showed up
right after you left.

453
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:53,520
That makes sense.

454
00:20:54,360 --> 00:20:55,640
I'll stay put this time.

455
00:21:03,360 --> 00:21:04,280
Got one!

456
00:21:05,040 --> 00:21:05,760
Nice size, too!

457
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:10,240
My rod!

458
00:21:12,760 --> 00:21:13,560
My rod!

459
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:15,960
Forget it. Don't go after it.

460
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:18,120
The water's deep and freezing.

461
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:19,200
Not worth it.

462
00:21:19,240 --> 00:21:20,080
No way.

463
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:21,400
I just bought that rod.

464
00:21:22,280 --> 00:21:23,080
If I lose it

465
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:24,280
and have to ask my wife for money again,

466
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:25,280
I'm done for.

467
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:27,760
Money's replaceable.

468
00:21:28,040 --> 00:21:29,480
Lose your life,
and that's a different story.

469
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:31,160
What kind of crap is that?

470
00:21:31,760 --> 00:21:32,560
Lose my life?

471
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:34,520
I'm not a kid.

472
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:35,600
This little bit of water?

473
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:37,680
I can walk through it blind.

474
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:45,760
Help!

475
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:47,720
I'm tangled in weeds!

476
00:21:47,920 --> 00:21:48,360
Help!

477
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:50,840
I'm stuck!

478
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,080
I warned you.

479
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:53,120
You didn't listen.

480
00:21:59,360 --> 00:21:59,800
Help!

481
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:05,920
Hello?

482
00:22:06,360 --> 00:22:07,240
Police?

483
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:08,520
I'm calling it in.

484
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:12,120
Someone's drowning here.

485
00:24:45,360 --> 00:24:46,840
Yeah, I warned him.

486
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:48,400
I told him the water was deep

487
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:49,400
and cold.

488
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:50,800
He didn't listen.

489
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:51,800
He even snapped at me.

490
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:53,160
When you saw he was in danger,

491
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:53,960
why didn't you help?

492
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:57,560
I can't swim.

493
00:24:57,800 --> 00:24:58,840
Is that wrong?

494
00:24:59,320 --> 00:25:00,200
That's not what I meant.

495
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:05,080
I called the police right away.

496
00:25:05,360 --> 00:25:06,680
It's just that this place
is really out of the way.

497
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:09,440
Is everything okay now?

498
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:10,120
If there's nothing else,

499
00:25:10,120 --> 00:25:11,000
can I go?

500
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:11,800
You can go.

501
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:13,520
If we need anything else,

502
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:14,440
we'll reach out.

503
00:25:14,840 --> 00:25:15,280
Alright.

504
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:23,160
Found him!

505
00:25:23,160 --> 00:25:24,080
We found the body!

506
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:38,240
Your Uncle Xiang brought this.

507
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:39,400
He just caught it today.

508
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:40,680
Came all this way to give it to us.

509
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:42,200
Cong,

510
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:43,680
you're back

511
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:45,600
at Customs now, right?

512
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:47,120
Perfect timing.
I caught this fish earlier.

513
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:49,440
I figured I'd bring it over
for you to try.

514
00:25:50,360 --> 00:25:51,160
Thanks.

515
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:53,800
Perfect way to celebrate being back.

516
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:09,120
Xiang,

517
00:26:09,320 --> 00:26:10,240
I need to say this.

518
00:26:10,480 --> 00:26:12,520
The way you're thinking is dangerous.

519
00:26:13,320 --> 00:26:15,800
You're basically excusing smugglers.

520
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:17,120
Since you brought them up,

521
00:26:17,120 --> 00:26:18,720
let's talk about those smugglers.

522
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:21,840
All these years,
you've been catching mules.

523
00:26:21,840 --> 00:26:23,080
So why did they become mules?

524
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:25,400
Because they got fooled
by smuggling rings.

525
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:27,760
They chased a little easy money,

526
00:26:27,760 --> 00:26:29,160
and it ended up ruining their lives.

527
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:31,640
Sounds like you pity them.

528
00:26:31,760 --> 00:26:32,680
How could I not?

529
00:26:33,280 --> 00:26:34,640
They were just tools,

530
00:26:34,640 --> 00:26:36,640
used to move contraband.

531
00:26:36,760 --> 00:26:38,560
Most don't know the law.

532
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:39,640
Some don't even know the truth.

533
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:40,480
Tell me that's not tragic.

534
00:26:40,600 --> 00:26:41,840
Choice.

535
00:26:42,800 --> 00:26:44,360
Chen, it's a matter of choice.

536
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:48,160
Just like you chose to join Customs,

537
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:50,640
they chose to be mules.

538
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:52,680
They chose to become tools for crime.

539
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:53,880
They don't deserve pity.

540
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:56,160
You're cold-hearted.

541
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:56,880
I'm not cold-hearted.

542
00:26:56,880 --> 00:26:58,120
I'm rational.

543
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:00,080
I understand them.

544
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:01,440
They have desires.

545
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:03,480
Unrealistic desires.

546
00:27:03,760 --> 00:27:04,520
They

547
00:27:04,640 --> 00:27:06,760
don't want to put in the work.

548
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:08,560
They want shortcuts.

549
00:27:08,880 --> 00:27:09,520
Then, someone

550
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:11,160
shows up and hands them a ladder.

551
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:12,360
Exactly.

552
00:27:12,480 --> 00:27:15,440
We need to catch the ones
handing out those ladders.

553
00:27:15,440 --> 00:27:18,360
Especially the handlers
inside these smuggling rings.

554
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:22,280
They're the kind of monsters
who devour people whole.

555
00:27:22,280 --> 00:27:22,720
You…

556
00:27:23,480 --> 00:27:25,400
[30 Minutes, Manual Measurement]

557
00:27:25,400 --> 00:27:26,200
Chen,

558
00:27:26,880 --> 00:27:28,640
do you remember what I asked you?

559
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:31,600
Can you really hold the line?

560
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:33,320
And for how long?

561
00:27:33,440 --> 00:27:34,600
You can't.

562
00:27:34,600 --> 00:27:36,000
No matter how long you try,
you can't hold it.

563
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:37,440
Not just you.

564
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:38,720
Cong can't either.

565
00:27:38,840 --> 00:27:40,200
And that trainee of his.

566
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:41,520
None of you can.

567
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:49,200
Enough.

568
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:51,960
I'll go get a doctor.

569
00:28:26,920 --> 00:28:27,560
[Dolls → Poisonous Perfume, E]

570
00:28:40,720 --> 00:28:41,360
Hurry…

571
00:28:41,840 --> 00:28:42,480
Hurry…

572
00:28:42,720 --> 00:28:43,240
Hurry…

573
00:28:43,760 --> 00:28:44,720
Today,

574
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:47,520
you've asked so many questions.

575
00:28:49,160 --> 00:28:49,880
Looks like

576
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:51,360
this

577
00:28:51,720 --> 00:28:52,880
might be

578
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:55,120
our last

579
00:28:55,560 --> 00:28:56,360
conversation.

580
00:28:58,760 --> 00:28:59,720
So let's just

